{"title_page": "Valley Girl (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Valley Girl\n| image          = Valley Girl poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Official poster\n| director       = [[Rachel Lee Goldenberg]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Matt Smith\n* [[Steven J. Wolfe]]\n}}\n| screenplay       = [[Amy Talkington]]\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Andrew Lane\n* Wayne Crawford\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jessica Rothe]]\n* [[Josh Whitehouse]]\n* [[Mae Whitman]]\n* [[Judy Greer]]\n}}<!--PER BILLING BLOCK-->\n| music          = [[Roger Neill]]\n| cinematography = Adam Silver\n| editing        = [[Julia Wong (film editor)|Julia Wong]]\n| production companies         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Orion Classics]]\n* [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n* Sneak Preview Productions\n}}\n| distributor    = [[United Artists Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|5|8|United States}}\n| runtime        =\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Valley Girl''''' is an upcoming American [[comedy film|comedy]] [[musical film|musical]] film, directed by [[Rachel Lee Goldenberg]], from a screenplay by [[Amy Talkington]] and story by Andrew Lane and Wayne Crawford. It is a remake of the 1983 film ''[[Valley Girl (1983 film)|Valley Girl]]'', it stars [[Jessica Rothe]],  [[Josh Whitehouse]], [[Mae Whitman]] and [[Judy Greer]].\n\nIt is scheduled to be released on May 8, 2020, by [[United Artists Releasing]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jessica Rothe]] as Julie Richman \n* [[Josh Whitehouse]] as Randy\n* [[Andrew Kai]]  as Rob\n* [[Chloe Bennet]] as Karen\n* Jessie Ennis as Stacey\n* [[Ashleigh Murray]] as Loryn\n* [[Logan Paul]] as Mickey\n* [[Mae Whitman]]\n* [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]] as Courtney\n* [[Allyn Rachel]] as Rachel Donahue\n* [[Josh Fadem]] as Gary\n* [[Danny Ramirez]] as Chip\n* Mary Neely as Felecia\n* Alex MacNicoll as Brad\n* Mario Revolori as Sticky\n* [[Alicia Silverstone]] as Older Julie\n* [[Camila Morrone]]\n* [[Judy Greer]]\n* [[Rob Huebel]]\n\n==Production==\nIn November 2016, it was announced [[Jessica Rothe]] would star in the film, with [[Rachel Lee Goldenberg]] would direct the film, from a screenplay by [[Amy Talkington]], with Matt Smith producing. [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]] will produce and distribute the film.<ref>{{cite web | first=Anita | last=Busch | title=MGM Taps Rachel Goldenberg To Helm Musical Adaptation Of \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 | url=http://deadline.com/2016/11/valley-girl-musical-remake-rachel-goldenberg-director-1201857104/ | website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] | date=November 18, 2016 | accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=N'Duka | first=Amanda | title=Jessica Rothe To Star In MGM\u2019s Musical Adaptation Of \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 | url=http://deadline.com/2016/11/jessica-rothe-valley-girl-mgm-1201861409/ | website=Deadline Hollywood | date=November 29, 2016 | accessdate=February 16, 2017}}</ref> In January 2017, [[Josh Whitehouse]] joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web | first=Mike | last=Fleming, Jr. | url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/valley-girl-musical-josh-whitehouse-nicolas-cage-mgm-poldark-1201877815/ | title=MGM Sets \u2018Poldark\u2019s Josh Whitehouse For \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Musical, In Nicolas Cage Role | website=Deadline Hollywood | date=January 3, 2017 | accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref>  In April 2017, [[Chloe Bennet]], [[Ashleigh Murray]], Jessie Ennis, and [[Logan Paul]] joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web |last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|title=\u2018Agents Of S.H.I.E.L.D.\u2019s Chloe Bennet, Logan Paul & More Join MGM\u2019s \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Remake|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/chloe-bennett-logan-paul-jessie-ennis-ashleigh-murray-valley-girl-mgm-1202077104/|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref> In May 2017, [[Mae Whitman]] also joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web | last=Kroll | first=Justin | title=\u2018Parenthood\u2019 Star Mae Whitman Joins \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Musical Remake (EXCLUSIVE) | url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/mae-whitman-valley-girl-remake-1202409144/ | work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date=May 4, 2017 | accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref> In June 2017, [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]] joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/valley-girl-peyton-list-mgm-1202106616/|title=MGM\u2019s \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Remake Adds Peyton List|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=June 2, 2017|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was scheduled to be released on June 29, 2018, however, it was pulled from the schedule, following [[Logan_Paul#2017\u20132018:_Suicide_forest_controversy|controversies surrounding Logan Paul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/logan-paul-valley-girl-release-date-change-1202307858/|title=\u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Remake With Controversial YouTuber Logan Paul Looking For Another Release Date|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=November 1, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref> It is scheduled to be released on May 8, 2020. It was originally supposed to be a theatrical release on that date, but was changed to a digital release due to the [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/valley-girl-remake-first-look/|title=Exclusive: Here's a, like, super rad look at the Valley Girl musical remake|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Devan|last=Coggan|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDB title|1266036}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American comedy films]]\n[[Category:American romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:American musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:American film remakes]]\n[[Category:Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rachel Lee Goldenberg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Valley Girl\n| image          = Valley Girl poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Official poster\n| director       = [[Rachel Lee Goldenberg]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Matt Smith\n* [[Steven J. Wolfe]]\n}}\n| screenplay       = [[Amy Talkington]]\n| story          = {{Plainlist|\n* Andrew Lane\n* Wayne Crawford\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jessica Rothe]]\n* [[Josh Whitehouse]]\n* [[Mae Whitman]]\n* [[Judy Greer]]\n}}<!--PER BILLING BLOCK-->\n| music          = [[Roger Neill]]\n| cinematography = Adam Silver\n| editing        = [[Julia Wong (film editor)|Julia Wong]]\n| production companies         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Orion Classics]]\n* [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n* Sneak Preview Productions\n}}\n| distributor    = [[United Artists Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|5|8|United States}}\n| runtime        =\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Valley Girl''''' is an upcoming American [[comedy film|comedy]] [[musical film|musical]] film, directed by [[Rachel Lee Goldenberg]], from a screenplay by [[Amy Talkington]] and story by Andrew Lane and Wayne Crawford. It is a remake of the 1983 film ''[[Valley Girl (1983 film)|Valley Girl]]'', it stars [[Jessica Rothe]],  [[Josh Whitehouse]], [[Mae Whitman]] and [[Judy Greer]].\n\nIt is scheduled to be released on May 8, 2020, by [[United Artists Releasing]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jessica Rothe]] as Julie Richman \n* [[Josh Whitehouse]] as Randy\n* [[Andrew Kai]]  as Rob\n* [[Chloe Bennet]] as Karen\n* Jessie Ennis as Stacey\n* [[Ashleigh Murray]] as Loryn\n* [[Logan Paul]] as Mickey\n* [[Mae Whitman]]\n* [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]] as Courtney\n* [[Allyn Rachel]] as Rachel Donahue\n* [[Josh Fadem]] as Gary\n* [[Danny Ramirez]] as 